<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="169">Major: pale to medium yellow; slender; antennal scape just reaching occipital border; occipital border deep, subangulate at midline; pilosity of body dorsum moderately abundant, suberect to erect, and very long; propodeal spine reduced to a denticle; pronotum and all of gaster smooth and shiny.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="169">Minor: occiput broad and lacking nuchal collar; propodeal spine reduced to a denticle; carinulae limited to circular lines around</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="169">antennal fossae; mesopleuron and side of propodeum foveolate and opaque; rest of body smooth and shiny.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="169">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.46, HL 1.62, SL 1.34, EL 0.26, PW 0.72.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="169">Paratype minor: HW 0.66, HL 0.82, SL 1.16, EL 0.22, PW 0.44.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="169">color Major: concolorous pale to medium yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="169">Minor: concolorous pale yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
